        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="381" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0023/1–347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-03T18:00:00+03:00">January 3, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 3—12:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Status of Dairen (Deptels 2208, December 31<note n="4" xml:id="d381fn1">See
                        telegram No. 1252, same date, to the Ambassador in China, <ref target="frus1946v10#pg_1200">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1946, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">x</hi>, p. 1200</ref>.</note> and 7, January 2).
                    Third person note containing substance of Dept’s 2208 sent to FonOff today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
